comment: Existence of a minimal element in certain classes: if ` R ` is well-founded and set-like on ` A ` , then every nonempty subclass of ` A ` has a minimal element. The proof has been taken from Chapter 4 of Don Monk's notes on Set Theory. See ~ http://euclid.colorado.edu/~~monkd/setth.pdf . (Contributed by Jonathan Ben-Naim, 3-Jun-2011.) (New usage is discouraged.)
